  @prompt
    Applying the New Vantage Co. Style
    Maintain a user-friendly four-column grid while replacing soft, rounded elements with your signature sharp, sophisticated aesthetic.
    
    1. Headline & Sub-headline
    
    Headline: Primary bold sans-serif font.
    Example: Shop By Frame Shape
    
    Sub-headline: Lighter body font offering guidance.
    Example: Unsure of your fit? Discover your perfect silhouette in our style guide. (link “style guide”)
    
    2. Grid of Cards
    
    Card Shape: Perfect rectangles with sharp 90-degree corners, preserving the brand’s architectural feel.
    
    Imagery: High-end product and model photography that is editorial and sophisticated. Clean, minimalist backgrounds let frame shapes stand out.
    
    3. Shape Labels
    
    Style: Solid black, semi-transparent rectangular bar at the bottom of each card.
    
    Typography: White, all-caps text with letter-spacing (e.g., 1.5px).
    
    Reinforces consistency with main buttons and premium visual language.
    
    Visual Description
    
    Section title: Bold headline Shop By Frame Shape.
    
    Grid: Four sharp-cornered images showcasing products.
    
    Example 1: Model wearing Cat-Eye frames with confident expression.
    
    Example 2: Minimalist Round frame against a textured background.
    
    Bottom of each card: Sleek black rectangular bar with shape names in crisp white, all-caps, elegantly spaced letters.
    
    First card: SQUARE
    
    Second: ROUND
    
    Third: CAT-EYE
    
    Fourth: RECTANGLE
    
    Impact
    This design creates a predictable, easy-to-navigate, and visually striking shopping experience while reinforcing New Vantage Co.’s premium, sharp, and sophisticated identity across the site., large portrait width everything nicely done and optimised for small screen
